The paper deals with reinforcement learning in multi-agent settings, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of value function factorization and communication learning techniques suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on multi-agent systems and coordination implies that it could also be classified under multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of communication minimization as a regularizer suggests that the paper could also be categorized under natural language processing (cs.CL).
